What you need to know:

Naturally, turkeys are good brooders and can hatch about 15 eggs.Brooding takes about 4-6 weeks from day-old, depending on the breed.Turkeys are susceptible to diseases and as such, deworming, vaccination and biosecurity measures are mandatory to prevent or slow down the spread of infections or disease-causing organisms.There is demand for turkey meat in the market in both dressed weight and whole bird, where toms of 10-20kg are sold at an average of Sh1,500 per kilo.